dcterms:creator: K. Bjarnadóttir
K. I. Hlynsdóttir
S. Steingrímsson
dcterms:description: The Database of Icelandic Morphology (DIM) contains a total of 2.9 million unique inflected forms, of which approximately 2.5 million are compounds. It is used for training a model to split Icelandic compound words into their constituent parts.
dcterms:title: Database of Icelandic Morphology (DIM)

dcterms:creator: K. Bjarnadóttir
K. I. Hlynsdóttir
S. Steingrímsson
dcterms:description: MorphIce is a morphological database that will contain the constituent structure of every word form in DIM. The preliminary version contains the constituent structures of approximately 2.9 million unique word forms.
dcterms:title: MorphIce

dcterms:creator: V. Henrich
E. Hinrichs
dcterms:description: GermaNet is a lexical-semantic resource for the German language that includes compound words manually annotated to indicate the position where a binary split occurs.
dcterms:title: GermaNet
